node.text: This cake from @sashimi1 is a stunning masterpiece. Each layer of this showstopping Lemon Chiffon Cake with Blueberry-Coriander Buttercream gets a lift from eggwhite-enriched cake batter and flavor-packed flourishes. Edible flower petals, mint leaves, pools of glistening jam, fresh berries, and sliced citrus channel serious summer vibes. Tap the link in bio for this epic layer cake recipe!

node.title: Lemon Chiffon Cake with Blueberry-Coriander Buttercream

node.text: The secret to these flavor-packed, plant-based nachos from @chefmamacass2 are two different kinds of lentils: black and red. Crispy pita chips are smothered with an the irresistable feta queso, layers of pepper-tinged lentil chili, rose harissa-spiked pickled cabbage, and dollops of yogurt. It's definitely a dish worth sharing. Tap the link in our bio for the recipe!

node.title: FWCooks | Loaded Pita Nachos with Lentil Chili and Feta Queso

node.text: This week F&W Culinary Director at Large @justinchapple  takes a cue from regional barbecue sauces to create three bold dressings to transform summer salads into hearty main dishes. Find out how to add some 'cue to your greens through the link in bio.

node.text: It can seem daunting to go out to eat if you’re someone with food allergies, but it shouldn't be. After all, @foodallergy reports that 85 million Americans are impacted by food allergies and 32 million of them deal with potentially life-threatening conditions. F&W Senior Editor @katkinsman spoke to chef, restaurateur, and national spokesperson for the Food Allergy and Anaphylaxis Network, Ming Tsai (@mingtsai), about things you can do to make your dining experience a little safer (and more enjoyable!). Tap the link in bio to read more.

node.text: Hardy enough to withstand braising and bold sauces, dried tofu skin sticks (doufu pi in Mandarin, yuba in Japanese) mimic the texture of shredded meat for an exciting addition to any vegetarian meal. In this Tofu Skin Stir-Fry recipe, soy, fried chile oil, mirin and sugar create an outstanding umami-rich sauce for the star of the dish.
